"title": "7944: ministry, qualifications for",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7944",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God, who calls his people to minister, also equips his people. The chief qualifications are a response to God's call, faithfulness, godliness and Christlikeness.</p>\n<h2>God calls people to minister</h2>\n<h3>Qualification is by call, not gifting or achievement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:7-Deut7:8\">DEU 7:7–7:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:4-Deut9:5\">DEU 9:4–9:5</a></p>\n<h3>God calls those who the world regards as weak or foolish</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:27-1Cor1:29\">1CO 1:27–1:29</a></p>\n<h3>Feelings of inadequacy to God's call are common</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:11\">EXO 3:11</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:15\">JDG 6:15</a> <em>Gideon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:21\">1SA 9:21</a> <em>Saul</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:18\">1SA 18:18</a> <em>David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:7\">1KI 3:7</a> <em>Solomon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:5\">ISA 6:5</a> <em>Isaiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:6\">JER 1:6</a> <em>Jeremiah</em></p>\n<h2>Responding to God's call to minister</h2>\n<h3>Readiness and availability</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam3:10\">1SA 3:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:8\">ISA 6:8</a></p>\n<h3>Faith, rather than natural talent or moral perfection, is required</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:1-Heb11:2\">HEB 11:1–11:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:19-Gen27:24\">GEN 27:19–27:24</a> <em>Jacob was a deceiver</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:12-Num27:14\">NUM 27:12–27:14</a> <em>Moses and Aaron disobeyed God.</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:4\">2SA 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:14-2Sam11:15\">2SA 11:14–11:15</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:9-1Kgs11:13\">1KI 11:9–11:13</a> <em>Solomon disobeyed God's command.</em></p>\n<h2>NT ministers are recognised by call rather than their achievement</h2>\n<h3>The Twelve</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1-Matt10:4\">MAT 10:1–10:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14-Mark3:19\">MRK 3:14–3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:12-Luke6:16\">LUK 6:12–6:16</a> <em>The Twelve, including Peter and Judas, failed Jesus Christ at critical times.</em></p>\n<h3>Paul</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:15\">ACT 9:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:6\">ACT 26:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:7-2Cor4:12\">2CO 4:7–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:7\">2CO 12:7</a> <em>Though greatly gifted, Paul was kept humble by his sense of unworthiness, difficulties and disappointments and his “thorn in the flesh”</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:16\">1TI 1:16</a></p>\n<h2>Ministry in the NT is described as service</h2>\n<h3>Serving God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:9\">ROM 1:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:1\">JAS 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>Serving Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1\">ROM 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:1\">JUD 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:1\">REV 1:1</a></p>\n<h3>Serving the gospel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:7\">EPH 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:23\">COL 1:23</a></p>\n<h3>Serving the church</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:31\">ROM 15:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:1\">ROM 16:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:15\">1CO 16:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:1\">2CO 9:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:21\">EPH 6:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:7\">COL 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:25\">COL 1:25</a></p>\n<h2>Ministry is described in terms of its source, content or nature</h2>\n<h3>Its source</h3>\n<p>It is of the Spirit:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:6\">2CO 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:8\">2CO 3:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:1\">2CO 4:1</a> <em>It is from God.</em></p>\n<h3>Its content</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2-Acts6:4\">ACT 6:2–6:4</a> <em>the word of God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18\">2CO 5:18</a> <em>reconciliation</em></p>\n<h3>Its nature</h3>\n<p>Apostolic:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:25\">ACT 1:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:8\">GAL 2:8</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:16\">ROM 15:16</a> <em>priestly</em></p>\n<h2>Various ministries are equally linked by qualifications of character</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:21\">ACT 1:21</a> <em>the replacement for Judas</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:3\">ACT 6:3</a> <em>the Seven</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:2-1Tim3:7\">1TI 3:2–3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:7-Titus1:9\">TIT 1:7–1:9</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:8-1Tim3:13\">1TI 3:8–3:13</a> <em>deacons</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:11\">1TI 6:11</a> <em>Timothy</em></p>\n<h2>The personal qualifications for ministry</h2>\n<h3>Faithfulness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:11-1Tim6:14\">1TI 6:11–6:14</a> <em>Timothy</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:7\">2TI 4:7</a> <em>Paul's claim for his own ministry</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:7\">COL 1:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:7\">COL 4:7</a></p>\n<h3>Godliness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:21\">ACT 8:21</a> <em>Simon was not right with God.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:11\">1TI 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20-1Tim6:21\">1TI 6:20–6:21</a></p>\n<h3>Christlikeness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:21-Acts1:22\">ACT 1:21–1:22</a> <em>The replacement apostle for Judas had to have been with Jesus Christ from the beginning.</em></p>",
